# Kubernetes Notes – Lecture 13
## Temporary (Ephemeral) Volumes & Projected Volumes

---

# Types of Kubernetes Volumes

```
Kubernetes Volumes
│
├── Temporary (Ephemeral Volumes)
│   ├── ConfigMap
│   ├── Secret
│   ├── Downward API
│   └── Projected Volume
│
└── Permanent (Persistent Volumes)
```

- **Temporary (Ephemeral) Volumes**
  - Exist only while the Pod is running.
  - Data is lost when the Pod is deleted.

- **Persistent Volumes**
  - Data survives Pod deletion.
  - Used for databases and long-term storage.

---

# ConfigMap

A **ConfigMap** stores non-sensitive configuration data.

Example:
- Application Name
- Color
- Environment
- Feature Flags

Instead of rebuilding the Docker image, configuration can be changed using ConfigMaps.

```
Predefined Image
       │
 Dockerfile
       │
 Kubernetes ConfigMap
```

---

## Step 1: Create a Configuration File

```bash
vi /tmp/app-config.txt
```

Contents:

```text
app=blue
color=Indian
```

---

## Step 2: Create ConfigMap

```bash
kubectl create configmap app-config \
--from-file=/tmp/app-config.txt
```

Check ConfigMap

```bash
kubectl get configmap app-config -o yaml
```

---

## Step 3: Mount ConfigMap as Volume

```yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: configmap-volume-pod
spec:
  containers:
  - name: nginx
    image: nginx
    volumeMounts:
    - name: config-volume
      mountPath: /etc/config
      readOnly: true

  volumes:
  - name: config-volume
    configMap:
      name: app-config
```

Create Pod

```bash
kubectl apply -f pod.yaml
```

---

## Verify Inside Container

```bash
kubectl exec -it configmap-volume-pod -- /bin/bash

df -hT

cd /etc/config

ls

cat app-config.txt
```

The ConfigMap data appears as files.

---

## Edit ConfigMap

```bash
kubectl edit configmap app-config
```

Change

```text
app=blue
color=Indian
```

to

```text
app=green
color=Indian
```

Verify

```bash
kubectl get configmap app-config -o yaml
```

### Important

- ConfigMap exists even if the Pod is deleted.
- When ConfigMap is mounted as a **Volume**, file contents update automatically after a short time.

