# ConfigMap Using Environment Variables

Create ConfigMap

```bash
kubectl create configmap app-env-config \
--from-literal=APP_COLOR=blue \
--from-literal=APP_MODE=production
```

Pod YAML

```yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: configmap-env-pod
spec:
  containers:
  - name: nginx
    image: nginx
    envFrom:
    - configMapRef:
        name: app-env-config
```

Check Environment Variables

```bash
kubectl exec -it configmap-env-pod -- /bin/bash

env
```

---

## ConfigMap Volume vs Environment Variable

| ConfigMap Volume | Environment Variable |
|------------------|----------------------|
| Updates automatically | Does not update automatically |
| No Pod restart required | Pod restart required |
| Appears as files | Appears as environment variables |

