# Secret

Secrets store **sensitive information**.

Examples

- Passwords
- API Keys
- Database Credentials
- Tokens

---

## Create Secret

```bash
kubectl create secret generic my-secret \
--from-literal=username=admin \
--from-literal=password='s3crtp@ss'
```

View Secret

```bash
kubectl get secret my-secret -o yaml
```

---

## Mount Secret as Volume

```yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: secret-volume-pod
spec:
  containers:
  - name: nginx
    image: nginx
    volumeMounts:
    - name: secret-volume
      mountPath: /etc/secret
      readOnly: true

  volumes:
  - name: secret-volume
    secret:
      secretName: my-secret
```

Inside container

```bash
kubectl exec -it secret-volume-pod -- /bin/bash

cd /etc/secret

ls

cat username

cat password
```

